{"updated_at": "2012-06-12T07:40:17Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-06-12T07:40:17Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6264785", "id": 6264785, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6685", "issue_id": 6685, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nahi/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/nahi", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nahi/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nahi/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nahi/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "6c06915d9aa00cd5c7d4acfb27cdd4e9", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nahi/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/nahi", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nahi/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/6c06915d9aa00cd5c7d4acfb27cdd4e9?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fcaea84e7e50ea556a7cd84ee1d0963a8.png", "id": 44209, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nahi/events{/privacy}", "login": "nahi", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nahi/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nahi/followers"}, "body": "autoload in CRuby 1.9.3 is NOT MT-safe. autoload in JRuby 1.6.6+ and CRuby 2.0.0dev should be MT-safe now.\n\nMy understanding is that Rails has two customized version of auto feature loading: \"customized autoload\" for production mode and \"on-demand file reloading\" for development mode. Per \"customized autoload\", it might be MT-safe on 1.6.6+ and 2.0.0dev. Per \"on-demand file reloading\", Rails needs some solution. (ClassLoader, MVM, or something)\n\n@josevalim, please let me know if you find that \"customized autoload\" (in production) is still NOT MT-safe.", "_id": {"$oid": "52380552bd3543c15100c703"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6685#issuecomment-6264785"}
